# Command skill

## What does this command do:

A TUI based command line skills chooser to be executed by Claude-code

## Installed from

For Fedora install using: `curl -L https://github.com/kevinpinscoe/skills-tui/releases/latest/download/skill-linux-amd64 -o ~/.local/bin/skill && chmod +x ~/.local/bin/skill`
For Raspberry Pi install using: `curl -L https://github.com/kevinpinscoe/skills-tui/releases/latest/download/skill-linux-arm64 -o ~/.local/bin/skill && chmod +x ~/.local/bin/skill`
For Mac install using: `curl -L https://github.com/kevinpinscoe/skills-tui/releases/latest/download/skill-darwin-arm64 -o ~/.local/bin/skill && chmod +x ~/.local/bin/skill`

## Command path

For Fedora run: `~/.local/bin/skill`
For Raspberry Pi run: `~/.local/bin/skill`
For Mac run: `~/.local/bin/skill`

## Command documentation

Docs can be found at https://github.com/kevinpinscoe/skills-tui

## Command options

# Launch the interactive TUI skill chooser
skill

# Show help
skill --help

# Set a custom skills root directory (default: ~/skills/skills)
SKILLS_DIR=<path> skill
